org.activebpel.rt.bpel.def.visitors
Class AeDefToImplVisitor

java.lang.Object
  org.activebpel.rt.bpel.def.visitors.AeDefToImplVisitor
All Implemented Interfaces:
IAeDefToImplVisitor, IAeDefVisitor
Direct Known Subclasses:
AeDefToBPWSImplVisitor, AeDefToWSBPELImplVisitor
public abstract class AeDefToImplVisitor
extends java.lang.Object
implements IAeDefToImplVisitor

Visitor responsible for creating implementation objects from their definition objects.

A static convenience method called createProcess has been setup to easily create a new process implementation.

traverse

protected void traverse(AeBaseDef aDef,
                        java.lang.Object aImpl)
Pushes the implementation onto the stack so it'll become the parent for any other activities created during the execution of this method. Then the def is visited which may call back into this class with other visit methods. Finally, we pop from the stack to restore the previous parent.
